stories: The objective of this paper is to provide a classification of multilingual and plurilingual electronic lexicographical resources which would allow, on the one hand, the implementation of quantitative and qualitative criteria to create a typological taxonomy of lexicographical tools such as dictionaries, as opposed to platforms and websites, and on the other, the distinction between multilingual and plurilingual resources in terms of their greater or lesser prototyping degree. In addition to offering a thorough description of the different resources, this paper also proposes parameters and typological proposals to define and demarcate a number of electronic resources, in particular multilingual dictionaries and portals, while also outlining, and even questioning, the object of study of multilingual and plurilingual lexicography.

In addition to describing the different resources, this paper also proposes parameters and typological proposals to define and demarcate a number of electronic resources, particularly multilingual dictionaries and portals, while outlining, and even questioning, the object of study of multilingual and plurilingual lexicography.
